dcterms:description: The Stanford Dogs dataset comprises 20,580 color images spanning 120 different dog breeds. These images were initially gathered from the ImageNet dataset. The dataset provides annotations, including class labels specifying the dog breed for each image and bounding box coordinates locating the dog within each image. However, for this work on image compression, only the image data itself was used.
dcterms:title: Stanford Dogs

dcterms:creator: C. Alessio
dcterms:description: The Animals 10 dataset comprises 26,200 images belonging to 10 categories: dog, cow, horse, elephant, butterfly, cat, chicken, sheep, spider, and squirrel. These images were obtained from Google Images.
dcterms:title: Animals 10

dcterms:creator: P. Roy
Saumik Bhattacharya

dcterms:description: The Natural Images dataset consists of images from various classes. Eight images were selected, one from each class, for testing.
dcterms:title: Natural Images
